lpers (mul, div, shift, round)\n53:- [ ] WS1-02 Implement integer exp/log/sqrt approximations\n54:- [ ] WS1-03 Implement integer softmax approximation\n55:- [ ] WS1-04 Implement RMSNorm (integer path)\n56:- [ ] WS1-05 Add test harness for math functions (compare against reference)\n58:### WS2 — GGUF Parser\n59:- [ ] WS2-01 Implement GGUF header parser (magic, version, tensor count, metadata count)\n60:- [ ] WS2-02 Implement GGUF metadata reader (key-value pairs, string/int/float/array types)\n61:- [ ] WS2-03 Implement GGUF tensor info reader (name, dims, type, offset)\n62:- [ ] WS2-04 Implement tensor data loader (read quantized blocks from file into memory)\n63:- [ ] WS2-05 Add GGUF validation tool (print model info, tensor list, total size)\n65:### WS3 — Quantization Kernels\n66:- [ ] WS3-01 Implement Q4_0 block structure (32 values per block, 1 scale float16)\n67:- [ ] WS3-02 Implement Q4_0 dequantize (block -> integer array)\n68:- [ ] WS3-03 Implement Q4_0 dot product (quantized vec * quantized vec -> scalar)\n69:- [ ] WS3-04 Implement Q8_0 block structure and dequantize\n70:- [ ] WS3-05 Implement Q8_0 dot product\n71:- [ ] WS3-06 AVX2 optimized Q4_0 dot product (inline asm)\n72:- [ ] WS3-07 AVX2 optimized Q8_0 dot product (inline asm)\n73:- [ ] WS3-08 Benchmark: Q4_0 dot product ops/sec (naive vs AVX2)\n75:### WS4 — Matrix Operations\n76:- [ ] WS4-01 Implement naive matmul (quantized input, integer accumulator)\n77:- [ ] WS4-02 Implement row-major / col-major layout handling\n78:- [ ] WS4-03 AVX2 tiled matmul (cache-friendly blocking)\n79:- [ ] WS4-04 Implement element-wise operations (add, mul, scale)\n80:- [ ] WS4-05 Benchmark: matmul GOPS for typical LLM dimensions (4096x4096)\n82:### WS5 — LLaMA Forward Pass\n83:- [ ] WS5-01 Implement RoPE (Rotary Position Embedding) in integer math\n84:- [ ] WS5-02 Implement GQA (Grouped Query Attention) — Q/K/V projection, score, softmax, output\n85:- [ ] WS5-03 Implement SwiGLU FFN (gate * up projection, silu activation,